---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
	title="Media and speaking"
	description="Press information for Steven Yule of OkArthur. Standard biography, photo, and topics for comment on digital, data and AI in infrastructure."
>
	<div class="page-head">
		<h1 class="page-title">Media and speaking</h1>
		<p class="lede">For journalists, producers and event organisers.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="prose reveal">
		<h2>Standard biography</h2>
		<p>
			Use this text verbatim. If space is short, cut from the end, not the
			middle.
		</p>
		<blockquote>
			Steven Yule is a chartered civil engineer providing independent advice
			on digital and AI in infrastructure and capital programmes. Based in
			Dubai, he has spent sixteen years across the Gulf and the UK making
			technology useful once it meets a live capital programme. Through
			OkArthur he reviews digital and AI investment decisions for owners, and
			advises boards. He is a Fellow of the Institution of Civil Engineers,
			an ICE Policy Fellow and ICE UAE Country Representative.
		</blockquote>

		<h2>Photo</h2>
		<img
			class="press-photo"
			src="/steven-yule.jpg"
			alt="Steven Yule, chartered civil engineer and independent adviser"
			width="1600"
			height="2463"
			loading="lazy"
		/>
		<p>
			This photo may be used for editorial coverage of Steven Yule or
			OkArthur. Credit is not required.
		</p>

		<h2>Topics</h2>
		<p>
			Comment, interviews and keynotes on digital, data and AI in
			infrastructure. Digital twins and what makes them worth relying on. AI
			investment decisions and the evidence behind them. What owners should
			test before a digital or AI procurement goes to market. Data in capital
			programme delivery and handover. Whole-life asset decisions.
		</p>

		<h2>Speaking</h2>
		<p>
			Recent talks, podcast appearances and published work are listed under <a
				href="/notes/">Notes</a
			>.
		</p>

		<h2>Enquiries</h2>
		<p>
			Email <a href="mailto:steven@okarthur.com">steven@okarthur.com</a> and
			mark it a press enquiry. Media requests get a same-day answer on
			availability.
		</p>
	</div>
</Base>
